===Sports parks===
There will be four “sports parks” throughout the city to host events at existing, temporary, and planned venues, as well as venues already under construction. The most prominent of the four locations will be the Downtown Sports Park, which will host events at various venues in [[Downtown_Los_Angeles|Downtown Los Angeles]]. The Downtown Sports Park will host events including swimming, diving, football, badminton, road cycling, fencing, taekwondo and basketball at Los Angeles City Hall and Grand Park, the Los Angeles Convention Center, Crypto.com Arena, Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum, and the campus of the [[University_of_Southern_California|University of Southern California]]. In addition to sporting events, the Downtown Sports Park will also host the Main Press Center, Media Village, and Olympic Family Hotels, and serve as the venue for the Opening and Closing Ceremonies.<ref name="gamesplan">{{cite web |url=https://la28.org/en/games-plan.html |title=Welcome to the LA28 Olympic and Paralympic Games |website=la28.org |access-date=20 August 2021 |url-status=live |archive-date=2022-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220221113426/https://la28.org/en/games-plan.html }}</ref>

